Svengaard had seen this building in the tricasts and entertainment vids.\~ He'd heard descriptions of the Hall of Counsel -- but actually to be standing here at the quarantine wall with the copper sheen of sunset over the hills across from it .\~.\~
. he'd never dreamed this could occur.
\par Elevator caps stood out like plasmeld warts on the hillock in front of him.\~ There were other low hills beyond with piled buildings on them that could've been mistaken for rock outcroppings.
\par A lone woman passed him on the esplanade pulling a ground-effect cart filled with oddly shaped bundles.\~ Svengaard found himself worried about what the bundles might contain, but he knew he dared not ask or show undue curiosity.
\par The red triangle of a pharmacy outlet glowed on a pillar beside him.\~ He passed it, glanced back at his escort.
\par He had come halfway across the continent in the tube with an entire car to himself except for the escort, an agent from T-Security.\~ Deep into Central they'd come, the gray-suited T-Security agent always beside him.
\par Svengaard began climbing the steps.
\par Already, Central was beginning to weigh on him.\~ There was a sense of something disastrous about the place.\~ Even though he suspected the source of the feeling, he couldn't shake it off.\~ 
It was all the Folk nonsense you could never quite evade, he'd decided.\~ The Folk were a people for the most part without legends or ancient myths except where such matters touched the Optimen.\~ In the Fol
k memories, Central and the Optimen were fixed with sinister omens compounded of awesome fear and adulation.
\par }{\i\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid14187295\charrsid14187295 Why did they summon me? }{\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid14187295\charrsid14187295 Svengaard asked himself.\~ The escort refused to say.
\par They were stopped by the wall and waited now, silent, nervous.
\par Even the agent was nervous, Svengaard saw.
\par }{\i\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid14187295\charrsid14187295 Why did they summon me?}{\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid14187295\charrsid14187295 
\par The agent cleared his throat, said, "You have all the protocol straight?"
\par "I think so," Svengaard said.
\par "Once you get into the hall, keep pace with the acolyte who'll escort you from there.\~ You'll be interviewed by the Tuyere -- Nourse, Schruille and Calapine.\~ Remember to use their names when you address them individually.\~ 
Use no such words as death or kill or die.\~ Avoid the very concepts if you can.\~ Let them lead the interview.\~ Best not to volunteer anything."
\par Svengaard took a trembling breath.
\par }{\i\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid14187295\charrsid14187295 Have they brought me here to advance me? }{\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid14187295\charrsid14187295 he wondered.\~ }{
\i\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid14187295\charrsid14187295 That must be it.\~ I've served my apprenticeship under such men as Potter and Igan.\~ I'm being promoted to Central.}{\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid14187295\charrsid14187295 

\par "And don't say 'doctor,'" the escort said.\~ "Doctors are pharmacists or genetic engineers in here."
\par "I understand," Svengaard said.
\par "Allgood wants a complete report on the interview afterward," the agent said.
\par "Yes, of course," Svengaard said.
\par The quarantine barrier lifted.
\par "In you go," the agent said.
\par "You're not coming with me?" Svengaard asked.
\par "Not invited," the agent said.\~ He turned, went down the steps.
\par Svengaard swallowed, entered the silver gloom of the portico, stepped through to find himself in the long hall with an escort of six acolytes, three to a side, swinging thuribles from which pink smoke wafted.\~ He smelled the antiseptics in the smoke.

\par The big red globe at the end of the hall dominated the place.\~ Its open segment showing flashing and winking lights; the moving shapes inside fascinated Svengaard.
\par The acolytes stopped him twenty paces from the opening and he looked up at the Tuyere, recognizing them through the power curtains -- Nourse in the center flanked by Calapine and Schruille.
\par "I came," Svengaard said, mouthing the greeting the agent had told him to use.\~ He rubbed sweaty palms against his best tunic.
\par Nourse spoke with a rumbling voice, "You are the genetic engineer, Svengaard."
\par "Thei Svengaard, yes .\~.\~. Nourse."\~ He took a deep breath, wondering if they'd caught the hesitation while he remembered to use the Optiman's name.
\par Nourse smiled.
\par "You assisted recently in the genetic alteration of an embryo from a couple named Durant," Nourse said.\~ "The chief engineer at the cutting was Potter."
\par "Yes, I was the assistant, Nourse."
\par "There was an accident during this operation," Calapine said.
\par There was a strange musical quality in her voice, and Svengaard recognized she hadn't asked a question, but had reminded him of a detail to which she wanted him to give his attention.\~ He felt the beginnings of a profound disquiet.
\par "An accident, yes .\~.\~. Calapine," he said.
\par "You followed the operation closely?" Nourse asked.
