\par "Yes?" he said.\~ "Oh, it's you."
\par "Something important's come up," she said.\~ "Svengaard's in the vat room examining the Durant embryo under microscope."
\par Allgood rolled his eyes.\~ "Oh, for the love .\~.\~.\~ Is that why you got me out of .\~.\~. is that why you called me?"
\par "But there was a noise and you said --"
\par "Forget it."
\par "I tell you there was a commotion of some kind in that room and now Doctor Svengaard's gone.\~ I didn't see him go."
\par "He probably left by another door."
\par "There is no other door."
\par "Look, sweetie, I have half a hundred agents there covering that room like a blanket.\~ A fly couldn't move in that room without our scanners picking it up."
\par "Then check with them to see where Svengaard's gone."
\par "Oh, for --"
\par "Check!"
\par "All right!"\~ Allgood turned to his hot line, got the duty agent.\~ The computer nurse could hear him through her open line.\~ "Where's Svengaard?"
\par A muffled voice responded, "Just went in and examined the Durant embryo under microscope, then left."
\par "Went out the door?"
\par "Just walked out."
\par Allgood's face came back onto the computer nurse's screen.\~ "You hear that?"
\par "I heard, but I've been down at the end of the hall ever since he went in.\~ He didn't come out."
\par "You probably turned your back for five seconds."
\par "Well .\~.\~."
\par "You did, didn't you?"
\par "I may've looked away just for a second, but --"
\par "So you missed him."
\par "But I heard a commotion in there!"
\par "If there was anything wrong, my men would've reported it.\~ Now, forget this.\~ Svengaard's no problem.\~ }{\i\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid14187295\charrsid14187295 They }{\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid14187295\charrsid14187295 
