\par Abruptly, he stood up, turned back to his bed.\~ The doxie playmate he'd brought in for the night lay there in the rosy light of a gloom dispeller, half awake, looking at him.\~ Her eyes under long lashes filled him with sudden rage.\~ 
"Get the hell out of here!" he roared.
\par She sat upright in the bed, wide awake, staring.
\par "Out!" he said, pointing to the door.
\par She tumbled out of bed, grabbed her clothing and ran out the door, a flash of pink flesh.
\par Only when she'd gone did Allgood realize who she'd reminded him of -- Calapine, a dull Calapine.\~ He wondered at himself then.\~
 The Cyborg had said the adjustments they made, the instruments they'd implanted, would help him control his emotions, permit him to lie with impunity even to Optimen.\~ This outburst now -- it frightened him.\~ He stared down at one of his slipper
s abandoned on the gray rug, its mate vanished somewhere.\~ He kicked the slipper, began pacing back and forth.
\par Something was wrong.\~ He could feel it.\~ He'd lived almost four hundred }{\i\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid14187295\charrsid14187295 lovely }{\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid14187295\charrsid14187295 
