 It should work if her system hasn't been too upset by all this."\~ He waved a hand indicating their flight, the emotional stress, the exertion.
\par "Do whatever you think you should," Harvey said.\~ "I know it's your best."
\par Svengaard administered the shot, patted Lizbeth's arm.\~ "Try to rest.\~ Relax.\~ Don't move around unless it's necessary."
\par Lizbeth nodded.\~ She had been reading Svengaard, seeing his genuine concern for her.\~ His attempt to reassure Harvey had touched her, but there were fears she couldn't suppress.
\par "Glisson," she whispered.
\par Svengaard saw the direction of her thoughts, and said, "I won't permit him to move you until I'm sure you're all right.\~ He and his guide will just have to wait."
\par }{\i\insrsid14187295 "You }{\insrsid14187295 won't permit!" Boumour sneered.
\par As though to punctuate his words, the ground around them rumbled and shook.\~ Dust puffed through the low entrance and, like a magician's trick, Glisson materialized there as the concealing dust settled.
\par At the first sign of disturbance, Harvey had dropped to the floor beside Lizbeth.\~ He held her shoulders, shielded her with his body.
