\par He looked up through the open segment of the Survey Globe at Calapine sitting alone on the dais of the Tuyere.\~ The lights of the interior played a slow rhythm across her face.\~ A glowing pyramid of projected binaries danced on the air in front of her.

\par Glisson had been released from his shell of restraint, but he still sat on the tumbril, his arm connections dangling empty.\~ A medicouch had been brought in for Lizbeth Durant.\~ She lay on it with Harvey seated beside her.\~
