\par Only Lizbeth, realizing her own bucolic docility in pregnancy, recognizing the flattening tenor of her emotions, suspected the }{\i\insrsid14187295 logical }{\insrsid14187295 fact which had swayed the Cyborg.\~ Docile people could be controlled.\~ That's
 what Glisson was thinking.\~ She could read it in him, understanding him fully for the first time now that she knew he had pride and anger.
